        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2024407036" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer598404020055362753">Chandler&apos;s 1939 classic crime novel is the first that featured Phillip Marlowe, the famous private detective who would appear in 7 of Chandler&apos;s novels. Humphrey Bogart brought him to life on the silver screen in the 1946 production of The Big Sleep. Even though it was written almost 80 years ago, it&apos;s not dated, meaning it has an almost modern feel to it. Good writing almost always equals good novel.</span>
  <span id="freeText598404020055362753" style="display:none">Chandler's 1939 classic crime novel is the first that featured Phillip Marlowe, the famous private detective who would appear in 7 of Chandler's novels. Humphrey Bogart brought him to life on the silver screen in the 1946 production of The Big Sleep. Even though it was written almost 80 years ago, it's not dated, meaning it has an almost modern feel to it. Good writing almost always equals good novel.</span>
